reviews.review_text:
Just Excellent Manor Downs was a great place to see the Dead and they always seemed to play well there.   Although great while you were there, it typically didn't yield very high quality AUD tapes--the open space seemed to just eat a lot of the dynamic range before it got to the tape.  

This is a very nice exception to the general rule.  The taper did a great job and then, of course, Charlie Miller-- saying he does a good job is like saying "nice smile on that painting, da Vinci."  

Really nice, extra-long Scarlet-Fire in this show--kind of loose, but very cool.  I thought Phil was usually mixed too low in the early 1980s, but not here-- he is in fine form and mixed loud enough to find the resonance frequency of two windows in my house on several occasions.  Get it.
cool show Very nice Loser - JG's voice is so very cool!
Longhorned Solid show.The sound is a little funkey but nice.You feel like your right in the audience.Strong 1st set closing with Mighty swell.Scarlet>Fire is ever so enjoyable.
